{
  "name": "Depression",
  "remarks": [
    "Major depressive disorder (MDD) in the general (non-veteran) population.",
    "Veterans are excluded because the veteran_mdd module already models MDD for patients ",
    "with the 'veteran' attribute; this module checks that attribute inside the annual onset ",
    "loop (veteran status is assigned by the veteran module in adulthood) and exits if it is set.",
    "",
    "Prevalence: lifetime prevalence of MDD in US adults is roughly 15-20%, and about twice as ",
    "high in women as in men. Sources: ",
    "Hasin DS et al. 'Epidemiology of Adult DSM-5 Major Depressive Disorder and Its Specifiers ",
    "in the United States.' JAMA Psychiatry. 2018;75(4):336-346 (lifetime prevalence 20.6%, ",
    "F:M roughly 2:1). ",
    "Kessler RC et al. 'Lifetime prevalence and age-of-onset distributions of DSM-IV disorders ",
    "in the National Comorbidity Survey Replication.' Arch Gen Psychiatry. 2005;62(6):593-602 ",
    "(lifetime MDD 16.6%; median age of onset 32, most first onsets between adolescence and ",
    "the mid-40s).",
    "",
    "Onset is modeled as an annual-probability loop from age 12 to age 50. ",
    "Female annual hazard 0.006 over ~38 at-risk years yields lifetime risk of about 20%; ",
    "male annual hazard 0.003 yields about 11%. Chronic medical comorbidity (diabetes, COPD, ",
    "CHF, opioid addiction - attributes actually set by other Synthea modules) modestly raises ",
    "the annual hazard, reflecting the well-documented association between chronic illness and ",
    "depression (Katon WJ, 'Epidemiology and treatment of depression in patients with chronic ",
    "medical illness', Dialogues Clin Neurosci. 2011;13(1):7-23).",
    "",
    "Course: episodic. Initial treatment is a first-line SSRI (sertraline, fluoxetine, or ",
    "escitalopram) plus a psychotherapy-oriented mental health care plan. About 30% of patients ",
    "do not respond to the first agent and are switched to venlafaxine (consistent with STAR*D ",
    "level-2 switching). During maintenance about 12% per quarter discontinue their ",
    "antidepressant without medical advice (non-adherence); most later resume care at a ",
    "follow-up visit. Remission occurs with probability 0.25 per quarter of treatment (median ",
    "treated episode roughly 9-12 months); the SSRI is continued 4-9 months after remission ",
    "before discontinuation, per APA practice guideline continuation-phase recommendations.",
    "",
    "Recurrence: after a first remitted episode, patients face a ~6%/year recurrence hazard ",
    "with a matching 6%/year chance of permanent recovery, so about 50% eventually experience ",
    "a recurrent episode (consistent with the commonly cited ~50% recurrence risk after a ",
    "single episode; Burcusa SL, Iacono WG. 'Risk for recurrence in depression.' Clin Psychol ",
    "Rev. 2007;27(8):959-985). Recurrent episodes are detected via PHQ-9 at a scheduled ",
    "wellness encounter.",
    "",
    "Attributes: sets 'depression' = true at first onset and intentionally KEEPS it true after ",
    "remission, so it acts as a lifetime history-of-depression marker that other modules (e.g. ",
    "anxiety) can key off - comorbidity correlations depend on history, not only on currently ",
    "active disease. The currently-active condition is tracked separately via the ",
    "'depression_condition' attribute (nil/ended when in remission). Also uses ",
    "'depression_careplan' and 'depression_med' internally.",
    "",
    "All SNOMED, LOINC, and RxNorm codes are reused from existing Synthea modules ",
    "(veteran_mdd, encounter/depression_screening, veteran_ptsd) except escitalopram ",
    "(RxNorm 349332) and venlafaxine (RxNorm 313586), which were verified against RxNav."
  ],
  "states": {
    "Initial": {
      "type": "Initial",
      "direct_transition": "Age_Guard"
    },
    "Age_Guard": {
      "type": "Guard",
      "remarks": [
        "Onset of MDD before adolescence is uncommon; the model starts the at-risk period at age 12."
      ],
      "allow": {
        "condition_type": "Age",
        "operator": ">=",
        "quantity": 12,
        "unit": "years"
      },
      "direct_transition": "Wait_For_Onset"
    },
    "Wait_For_Onset": {
